Light Neutral Theme with Sidebar:

Background Color (Main Content): #F5F5F5
Sidebar Color: #DADADA
Accent Color: #B0B0B0
Text Color: #333333
Button Shades:

Primary Button: #B0B0B0
Secondary Button: #979797
Disabled Button: #D9D9D9
Text Input Shades:

Active Input Border: #B0B0B0 (slightly darker than the background color)
Placeholder Text: #808080
Input Text: #333333
Card or Panel Shades:

Use variations of #F5F5F5 for the main content area with subtle differences for depth.
Icon Shades:

Use shades that are slightly darker or lighter than the background color. For example, you might use #CCCCCC for icons.

Profile Card in Sidebar:

Card Background Color: #DADADA (same as the sidebar background)
Text Color: #333333 (for readability against the card background)
To create a subtle visual separation between the card and the sidebar background, you might consider using a slightly lighter or darker shade for the card background. For example:

Lighter Card Background Shade: #D0D0D0
Darker Card Background Shade: #C5C5C5

Form Card:

Form Card with Color:

Card Background Color: #F2F9F4 (a light and fresh shade)
Border Color: #B0D3C1 (a slightly darker shade for a subtle border)
Text Color: #333333
Input Fields:

Input Background: #E6F3EC (a light shade with a hint of color)
Placeholder Text: #86BFA5 (a muted, complementary color)
Submit Button:

Button Background: #4CAF50 (a vibrant green for the submit button)
Text Color: #FFFFFF (white for better contrast)

Total Component Card:

Card Background Color: #F5F5F5 (similar to the main content area)
Border Color: #DADADA (a slightly darker shade for a subtle border)
Text Color: #333333
